title: For Sale:  Rare Egyptian UAE Rasheed Carbine 7.62X39 Hakim
postcontent: It is Rare Egyptian UAE Rasheed Carbine 7.62X39 Hakim all numbers are matching, but I'm not very good at reading Arabic. The bluing on the rifle looks good, with some wear. Barrel bore is shiny and lands look good. Barrel is threaded and has the correct barrel nut to match up with the bayonet. Wood looks to be crack-free, with some dings on the body from use. Buttplate has a few typical dings, with some deformation of the wood around it. Action is smooth and still needs the residual Cosmolene cleaned out. Magazine locks up tight and the bolt hold-open functions correctly. Not much wear in that area,Overall a great collectible rifle. Shipping available. Ask for more pictures. The Egyptian Rasheed Carbine (also "Rashid") was born from the Hakim Rifle which, in turn, was born from the Swedish Ljungman AG-42 semi-automatic rifle line. The Ag-42 rifle was produced for the Swedish Army during World War 2 (1939-1945) and entered service in 1942. The weapon was a gas-operated, repeating rifle system utilizing the local 6.5x55mm cartridge. After the war, the Egyptian government secured the rights to the rifle and purchased the required machining tools for local production of the type - this becoming the Hakim Rifle of the 1950s with chief changes being its now-adjustable gas function and chambering for the 7.92x57mm Mauser. The Rasheed was a further-developed form of the Hakim though shortened into a more handy carbine form. Production numbers totaled only 8,000 units and adoption occurred in 1960.

title: For Sale:  Hi Point C9
postcontent: Like new 9mm Hi Point C9 compact, has less than 100 rounds shot.  I bought this on sale at Cabelas in OKC.  Although it is heavy and ugly, I've been very surprised at how reliable and accurate it shoots.  Comes with the original hard case, trigger lock, two magazines, extra set of ghost ring sights, and a limited edition kershaw pocket knife.  I also installed traction grips.  An excellent gun for the money.Cash only, no trades or shipping.   Must provide an Oklahoma photo ID, CCW preferred.If interested, please contact me, nine one eight 206-five eight one seven.
